The total cases of coronavirus in Nigeria are now put at 542 with the confirmation of 49 new cases yesterday. Also, total deaths from the virus has now been put at 19. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control stated this in its official tweeter handle, stating that a total of 166 recoveries have been recorded. “59 new cases of COVID-19 have been reported; 23 in Lagos, 12 in FCT, 10 in Kano, 2 in Ogun, 1 in Oyo, 1 in Ekiti. As at 10:40 pm 18th April there are 542 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported in Nigeria,” NCDC said. 